00:00:49.100 --> 00:00:52.260
Firstly let's talk about resolution,

00:00:52.260 --> 00:00:56.600
the resolution is the amount of
information thats captured on the camera sensor,

00:00:56.600 --> 00:00:59.910
it would affect the size and the quality
of your picture.

00:00:59.910 --> 00:01:03.750
The higher the resolution the
better-quality the picture.

00:01:03.750 --> 00:01:06.750
the lower resolution, the lower the quality. Now

00:01:06.750 --> 00:01:11.010
the thing about resolution is that its
only as good as the device you're going

00:01:11.010 --> 00:01:12.299
to be playing it back on,

00:01:12.299 --> 00:01:18.140
so if you can be playing your video is
back on 4k high-definition television

00:01:18.140 --> 00:01:21.750
then you'll want to set the resolution
on your camera 4k

00:01:21.750 --> 00:01:25.070
because the quality will be justified However

00:01:25.070 --> 00:01:28.270
if your videos are going to end up on
YouTube or Facebook,

00:01:28.270 --> 00:01:31.549
then you don't need to shoot at such a
high resolution because all you'll do

00:01:31.549 --> 00:01:35.409
is use up memory, so you shoot at an
appropriate resolution.

00:01:35.409 --> 00:01:39.650
As you can see from this clip the
picture is super crisp and clear

00:01:39.650 --> 00:01:43.840
with detail in the blacks and whites and
lot of good color representation,

00:01:43.840 --> 00:01:48.640
in what are actually a challenging range
of colors. This is fantastic quality

00:01:48.640 --> 00:01:52.500
and great if you want to speed up footage,
show it on a 4k TV

00:01:52.500 --> 00:01:56.820
or even take high-quality 8 megapixel
stills from your footage.

00:01:56.820 --> 00:02:01.750
At the other end of the scale you can
shoot at a resolution of 720

00:02:01.750 --> 00:02:05.329
and you've got a choice of fields of view, of
narrow, medium

00:02:05.329 --> 00:02:08.000
and wide and even super wide

00:02:08.000 --> 00:02:11.700
and you can shoot at 25, 24, 50,

00:02:11.700 --> 00:02:16.660
or 100 frames a second. Now this stuff
isn't going to be as good as the 4k

00:02:16.660 --> 00:02:17.340
quality

00:02:17.340 --> 00:02:21.760
