00:02:32.280 --> 00:02:33.860
Right frames per second,

00:02:33.870 --> 00:02:37.090
now the frames per second rate that you shoot at

00:02:37.090 --> 00:02:41.670
is really important to your footage. All standard videos

00:02:41.670 --> 00:02:46.800
either run at 25 or 24 frames a second, this
is the number of pictures

00:02:46.800 --> 00:02:52.000
that the video takes each second to give you a smooth movement.

00:02:52.000 --> 00:02:55.000
Now if you shoot at 25 frames per second

00:02:55.010 --> 00:02:59.080
and then play it back at 25 frames per
second it runs at normal speed,

00:02:59.080 --> 00:03:03.900
if you shoot 50 frames a second and then
play that video back at 25 frames a

00:03:03.900 --> 00:03:04.410
second,

00:03:04.410 --> 00:03:09.680
your video will run at half speed. This is
how you get slow motion and this is why

00:03:09.680 --> 00:03:11.020
the frames per second

00:03:11.020 --> 00:03:16.300
are so important when you're shooting on
your GoPro. If you want super slow motion

00:03:16.300 --> 00:03:20.090
you can shoot at 100 frames per second
and that will allow you to slow it down

00:03:20.090 --> 00:03:26.220
four times and still be a really lovely
smooth peace video, even

00:03:26.220 --> 00:03:29.700
on the WVGA  setting, you can shoot

00:03:29.700 --> 00:03:33.150
at 240 frames per second which will give you

00:03:33.150 --> 00:03:36.170
super slow motion. I use this setting

00:03:36.170 --> 00:03:40.190
WVGA at 240 frames per second to shoot
this clip

00:03:40.190 --> 00:03:43.239
